               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 3 items (a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous works on Chishti Sufism and poetry. Volume not dated; items band c dated, 17 Ṣafar-19 Rabīʿ I 1149/27 June-28 July 1736. Large and rough scribal nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz hands. Stamped foliation. Lacks original covers. Binding damaged and detached from gathering; leather boards with exterior edged with narrow band of gilt tooled Greek key design, doublure of pebble marbled paper with leather edged in narrow band of gilt tooled floral scroll. Original European-style opening bears the ex libris of John Lyall Findon (motto: An I May), reused and inverted with the addition of Persian paper labels on exterior. Folios unbound, stains, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile. IOL microfilm detailed below. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1175-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="85v">ff. 1v-85v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Incomplete fragment of an untitled Ṣūfī mas̲navī by an unnamed author breaking off abruptly without conclusion. </p>
                        <p>Defective at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Text organised in irregular multidirectional layouts. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1175-item2">
                     <locus from="88v" to="128v">ff. 88v-128v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22212">Risālah vujūdīyah</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Treatise on the Chishtī branch of Qādirī Sufism ascribed to the saint, <persName key="person_f7234" role="att">Khvājah Muʿīn al-Dīn Chishtī Sijzī</persName>, although this is considered improbable by Levy. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 128v): 17 Ṣafar in RY 18 of <persName key="person_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName>, 1149/27 June 1736. 
                        </p>
                        <p>See IOL microfilm 38. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1175-item3">
                     <locus from="129r" to="134r">ff. 129r-134r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on Sufism quoting a large number of poems in support, by an unnamed author. 
</p>
                        <p>The work terminates with the quotation of a Hindi verse by <persName key="person_f7204" role="asn">Kabīr</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 134r): completed by <persName key="person_f7061" role="scr">Ākhūnd ʿAbd al-Vāsiʿ</persName> at the order of a certain <persName key="person_f7519" role="pat">Sativāsī Baygum'jīv</persName>, Sunday, 19 Rabīʿ I in RY 18 of <persName key="person_45680638" role="oth">Emperor Muḥammad Shāh</persName>, (1149)/28 July 1736. 
                        </p>
                        <p>See IOL microfilm 38. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
